你投我以桃，我报你以李。
You give me a peach, and I give you a plum.
有一种报恩，叫以善回应善。
There is a recompense for goodness.
全文1281字，阅读约需2.5分钟新型肺炎疫情爆发以来，“一方有难，八方支援”的温暖故事每天都在上演，不少人用实际行动为武汉加油，也见证着社会互助的力量。
Since the outbreak of the new type of pneumonia in about 2.5 minutes, the warm story of "support from all sides" is playing out every day. Many people cheer Wuhan with their actions and bear witness to the power of mutual social assistance.
这两天，就有6辆从四川汶川开往武汉的卡车，谱写了一份跨越时空的感动。
In the past two days, there are six trucks from Wenchuan to Wuhan, Sichuan, write a moving across time and space.
▲人民日报客户端视频截图很多人对于汶川最深刻的记忆，依旧停留在2008年。
People's Daily client video screenshots of Wenchuan for many of the most profound memories, still in 2008.
地震后，四川省汶川县100多名伤者被送到武汉多家医院，接受免费救治。
After the earthquake, more than 100 injured people in Wenchuan County, Sichuan Province, were taken to Wuhan hospitals, receiving free medical treatment.
在武汉市各大医院的医生们精心照料下，所有伤者无死亡、无感染、无后遗症。
Under the meticulous care of doctors at major hospitals in Wuhan, none of the injured died, were infected and had no sequelae.
你投我以桃，我报你以李。
You give me a peach, and I give you a plum.
有一种报恩，叫以善回应善。
There is a recompense for goodness.
这次疫情发生后，四川汶川县的村民们，就自发支援武汉，主动捐赠了100吨蔬菜。
After the outbreak, Sichuan Wenchuan County villagers, on their own initiative to support Wuhan, donated 100 tons of vegetables.
12位村民驾驶6辆卡车出发，他们日夜兼程，26小时后，卡车上100吨新鲜蔬菜，运送到了武汉市的9个医院和外省医疗队驻地。
Twelve villagers, driving six trucks, travelled day and night and, 26 hours later, 100 tons of fresh vegetables were loaded onto trucks and transported to nine hospitals and provincial medical team sites in Wuhan city.
▲人民日报客户端视频截图在这6辆卡车上，还贴着一句话，用以纪念这份跨越时空的感动：“汶川感恩您 武汉要雄起”。
People's Daily client video screenshot on the six trucks, but also posted a sentence to commemorate the time-span of the move: "Wenchuan Thanksgiving you Wuhan to rise.
他们说：“作为汶川人，最应该感恩！”此消息一出，不少网友第一时间表达了对汶川人的感谢和赞赏。
They said: "As Wenchuan people, the most should be grateful!" This news, many netizens first expressed their thanks and appreciation to Wenchuan people.
▲微博截图汶川村民12年后仍不忘曾经受到的帮助，及时支援武汉，小编也深受感动。
Wenchuan Weibo screenshot Wenchuan village 12 years later still remember the help received, timely support to Wuhan, small editor also deeply moved.
其实，不仅是汶川村民，面对疫情，还有很多曾经接受过帮助的人，时刻心系同胞，希望能够尽其所能，一起度过这段艰难的时期。
In fact, not only Wenchuan villagers, in the face of the epidemic, there have been a lot of people who have received help, always heart-to-heart compatriots, hope to be able to do their best together through this difficult period.
佘沙除了是一名普通护士外，还有一个特殊的身份，她是汶川地震的幸存者。
She Sha besides is an ordinary nurse, also has a special status, she is Wenchuan earthquake survivor.
12年前，她的家乡遭受了重创，是四面八方的大爱汇聚，将她从废墟中托了起来。
Twelve years ago, her hometown was hard hit, a gathering of love from all sides, lifted her from the ruins.
12年后，在又一场灾难袭来之时，她挺身而出，报名备战。
Twelve years later, when another disaster struck, she stepped forward and signed up.
她说：“这几天看新闻，我想到了汶川地震的场景，我觉得我应该去。
"I've been watching the news these days and I think about the Wenchuan earthquake and I think I should go," she said.
因为我和其他护士不一样，我是汶川人呀！”▲佘沙宣誓。
Because I and other nurses are different, I am Wenchuan ah! She Sha oath.
图片来自中新社45岁的周仁刚是一名三轮车夫，汶川地震后，因为要修补房屋，他不慎跌倒导致颈部受伤。
Chow Yan Gang, 45, is a rickshaw man who was injured in the neck after an earthquake in Wenchuan after falling to repair his house.
来自全国各地的救援和帮助，让他重拾信心。
Rescue and help from all over the country reassured him.
当新型肺炎疫情肆虐之际，他捐出了2万元积蓄用于疫情防控。
When the new pneumonia epidemic raged, he donated 20, 000 yuan to fund disease control.
因为“我曾经受过社会各界对我的关爱，现在武汉有难了，我也要为她加油。
Because "I have been the community of my love, now Wuhan has trouble, I also want to cheer for her.
”▲图片来自微博。
The pictures came from Weibo.
还有90后的川妹子王利，在汶川地震中逃过生死劫难。
There are 90 sisters Wang Li, in Wenchuan earthquake escaped the fate of the disaster.
她说现在每多活的一天，都是赚来的。
She said that every day she lived was now earned.
在武汉封城前，她选择留下，做了一名志愿者。
Wuhan in front of the city, she chose to stay, as a volunteer.
每天早上8点半，王利准时报到，帮居民采买生活必需品，接送重症患者就医，为社区运输防护保障物资。
Every morning at 8: 30, Wang Li-zhun reports to help residents collect necessities, transport patients with serious medical conditions, and transport protective materials for the community.
厚厚的防护服下，只露出一双明亮的眼睛，这位“90后”姑娘坚定地说：“那时候全国都在帮汶川，现在全国都在帮武汉。
The thick protective clothing, only a pair of bright eyes, the "90 after" girl firmly said: "At that time the whole country was helping Wenchuan, now the whole country is helping Wuhan.
我是过来人，只要所有人团结一心，就一定能渡过难关”。
I am a passing person, as long as all together, will be able to tide over difficulties. "
▲图片来自央视新闻。
Images come from CCTV News.
正如网友所言：“不知道这场疫情还要持续多久，但相信黎明的那道光，一定会越过黑暗，因为有无数的人在逆风前行。
As netizens have said: "I do not know how long this epidemic will continue, but believe that the light of the dawn, will cross the dark, because there are countless people in the wind.
”小编也相信，互助的力量，终将会战胜疫情，为我们带来数不尽的好消息。
The editor also believes that the power of mutual help will eventually overcome the epidemic, bringing us untold good news.
